ðŸ”¹ Section 2: Using ALL
Get employees whose salary is greater than ALL employees in the HR department.
select *  from Employees where salary > all ( select  salary from  Employees where department = 'hr');
+--------+--------+--------+------------+
| emp_id | name   | salary | department |
+--------+--------+--------+------------+
|      8 | Hannah |  75000 | IT         |
+--------+--------+--------+------------+
Find employees whose salary is less than ALL employees in the IT department.
select *  from Employees where salary < all ( select salary from Employees where department = 'it');
+--------+-------+--------+------------+
| emp_id | name  | salary | department |
+--------+-------+--------+------------+
|      1 | Alice |  50000 | HR         |
|      6 | Frank |  52000 | Finance    |
|      7 | Grace |  48000 | HR         |
|      9 | Ian   |  50000 | Sales      |
+--------+-------+--------+------------+


Find employees whose salary is equal to ALL employees in the Sales department.
select  * from Employees where salary = all (select  salary from Employees where department = 'Sales');
